<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 04 at 2:09PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Comanche,
southern Caddo and northwestern Cotton Counties through 245 PM CDT...
At 209 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Faxon, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lawton, Elgin, Geronimo, Fletcher, Sterling, Chattanooga, Faxon,
southeastern Lake Ellsworth and eastern Fort Sill.
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 23 and 62.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
